    static class IeeeConversionTesterClasses.QuadToIEEELongsTester
extends TesterClasses.Conversion_Q2T_Tester<long[]>
    A tester class to test Quadruple.toIeee754Longs().
    Obtains the test data from IeeeConversionTesterClasses.q2ieeeConversionDataList() and performs Quadruple.toIeee754Longs() as the tested operation.

      • findExpectedString

        protected String findExpectedString(Quadruple operand)
        Returns string representations ("Infinity" or "-Infinity" or "NaN") for values that don't fall within the range allowed for IEEE-754 Quadruple. Values too large for IEEE quadruple are also too large for double, so using double to format such values is OK.
        Overrides:
        findExpectedString in class TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester<Quadruple,long[]>
        Parameters:
        operand - not used in the default implementation
        Returns:
        the default implementation returns null. Specific descendants that require this method should provide a proper value.

      • findExpectedResult

        protected BigDecimal findExpectedResult(Quadruple operand)
        Calculates a BigDecimal value of the expected result of the conversion from Quadruple to long[].
        The expected result is the input value rounded to the exact value of the nearest IEEE-754 Quadruple, expressed as a BigDecimal. Throws NumberFormatException for values that can't be represented as BigDecimal: NaN, Infinity, and -Infinity.
        Overrides:
        findExpectedResult in class TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester<Quadruple,long[]>
        Parameters:
        operand - the value to be converted
        Returns:
        the expected result of the tested operation as a BigDecimal
